# Description:
hda2csg is a function that maps a couple (hda, pn), where hda is the maxcell representation of the higher-dimensional automaton (HDA) for the Petri-net (PN) pn, to the corresponding concurrent step graph (CSG) of the HDA.

## Dependencies:
Require the modules spot (https://spot.lre.epita.fr/index.html), argparse, dataclasses, subprocess, glob and pathlib.

## Usage:
Run "python3.12 hda2csg.py pn_file.pnml io_file.txt" to output the controler in Hanoi Omega-Automata format(https://spot.lre.epita.fr/hoa.html).

The function build_csg_from_files() builds the controller from the specification files for the hda, the Petri net and the input/output.

### Example:
python3.12 hda2csg.py ../pnml_files/basic/abx_squared.pnml io_example.txt
